2 Word and character distribution

2.1 nchar distribution

2.2 unnest text to word

data(stop_words)
unnested <- tweets %>%
    mutate(text = str_replace_all(text, "https://t.co/[A-Za-z\\d]+|&amp;", "")) %>%
    unnest_tokens(word, text, token = "regex", pattern = "[^A-Za-z\\d#@']", drop=FALSE) %>%
    anti_join(stop_words)
Joining, by = "word"

2.3 sorted by word frequency

unnested %>%
    count(word) %>%
    mutate(word = reorder(word, n)) %>%
    top_n(50) %>%
    mutate(ismedia = ifelse(str_detect(word, "@.*|#.*"), "ismedia", "other")) %>%
    ggplot(aes(word, n, fill=ismedia)) + 
    geom_col() + 
    coord_flip() + 
    scale_fill_manual(values=c("ismedia"="tomato", "other"="gray"), guide=F)
Selecting by n

2.4 word frequency distribution

unnested %>%
    count(word) %>%
    count(n) %>%
    ggplot(aes(n, nn)) + 
    geom_col() + 
    ggtitle("Word frequency distribution") + 
    xlab("word frequency") + ylab("Distribution") + 
    theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

  • Number of words per doc.
unnested %>%
    count(id) %>%
    ggplot(aes(n))  + 
    geom_histogram()

3 Sentiment analysis

library(tidytext)
sentiments
  • The three general-purpose lexicons are
    • afinn from Finn rup Nielsen,
    • bing from Bing Liu and collaborators, and
    • nrc from Saif Mohammad and Peter Turney.
get_sentiments("afinn")
get_sentiments("bing")
get_sentiments("nrc")
unnested %>%
    count(word) %>%
    inner_join(get_sentiments("afinn")) %>%
    arrange(desc(n)) %>%
    slice(1:50) %>%
    mutate(PN = ifelse(score > 0, "positive", "negative")) %>%
    mutate(word = reorder(word, n)) %>%
    ggplot(aes(word, n, fill=PN)) + 
    geom_col() + 
    coord_flip()
Joining, by = "word"

unnested %>%
  inner_join(get_sentiments("bing")) %>%
  count(word, sentiment, sort = TRUE) %>%
  acast(word ~ sentiment, value.var = "n", fill = 0) %>%
  comparison.cloud(colors = c("royalblue", "tomato"),
                   max.words = 100)
Joining, by = "word"

library(lubridate)
summary(tweets$created)
                 Min.               1st Qu.                Median 
"2015-12-14 20:09:15" "2016-03-22 21:50:44" "2016-05-18 00:43:37" 
                 Mean               3rd Qu.                  Max. 
"2016-05-12 00:18:06" "2016-07-02 04:04:08" "2016-08-08 15:20:44" 
tweets.sentiment <- unnested %>%
    inner_join(get_sentiments("bing")) %>%
    count(id, sentiment) %>%
    spread(sentiment, n, fill=0) %>%
    mutate(sentiment=positive-negative) %>%
    left_join(tweets, by="id") %>%
    arrange(created) %>%
    mutate(tindex=1:n())
Joining, by = "word"
